items.name: create-module-wise-repository
items.description: Run  php artisan module:make-repository {repositoryName} {moduleName} --model={modelName} --interface={interfaceName}. Repository and module name are mandatory. Model and interface name are optional.

items.name: ImgResources
items.description: Since the code on GitHub is inconsistent with the local code when Git is used to upload the code, various extra operations are needed, so this repository is specially created to store the images used in various projects. The name format is  repositoryName _ pathToTheFilesInTheRepository.

items.name: CS7NS1-RestServiceAPI
items.description: REST service that provides an interface for submitting a set of GitHub repositories (identified as a list of strings of the form  “username/repositoryname”). Service identify the set of GitHub developers who have contributed to any of these repositories in 2018.
